hm2FileMgmtMib.name: hm2FileMgmtMib

hm2FMActionTable.name: hm2FMActionTable
hm2FMActionTable.description: A list of profiles stored in NV memory.

hm2FMActionType.name: hm2FMActionType
hm2FMActionType.description: Type of the action to be performed.

hm2FMActionItemType.name: hm2FMActionItemType
hm2FMActionItemType.description: Type of the item to be processed.

hm2FMActionSourceType.name: hm2FMActionSourceType
hm2FMActionSourceType.description: Type of the source object to be processed.

hm2FMActionDestinationType.name: hm2FMActionDestinationType
hm2FMActionDestinationType.description: Type of the destination object to be processed.

hm2FMActionActivate.name: hm2FMActionActivate
hm2FMActionActivate.description: In case of a set operation: If the value to be written matches with the result of hm2FMActionActivateKey, the action is started. In case of a read operation, it will always reflect the key of the last successful operation.

hm2FMActionSourceData.name: hm2FMActionSourceData
hm2FMActionSourceData.description: Additional data for the source object. This could, for example, be a profile name or URL

hm2FMActionDestinationData.name: hm2FMActionDestinationData
hm2FMActionDestinationData.description: Additional data for the source object. This could be for example a profile name or URL

hm2FMActionActivateResult.name: hm2FMActionActivateResult
hm2FMActionActivateResult.description: Either returns ok(1) if the action is successfully started, param-error(2) if there is some problem with the given parameters or busy(3) if there is still an action in progress.

hm2FMActionActivateResultText.name: hm2FMActionActivateResultText
hm2FMActionActivateResultText.description: Text describing why the start of the operation has failed.

hm2FMActionStatus.name: hm2FMActionStatus
hm2FMActionStatus.description: Returns the running status of the action.

hm2FMActionPercentReady.name: hm2FMActionPercentReady
hm2FMActionPercentReady.description: Estimation of how many percent of the operation is done.

hm2FMActionResult.name: hm2FMActionResult
hm2FMActionResult.description: Error status of the last action which has been performed.

hm2FMActionResultText.name: hm2FMActionResultText
hm2FMActionResultText.description: Either OK or a descriptive text giving a reason why the last operation failed

hm2FMActionActivateKey.name: hm2FMActionActivateKey
hm2FMActionActivateKey.description: An advisory lock used to ensure that different management entities can not interfere with each others actions. The value read from this variable must be used to start the action by applying to the object hm2FMActionActivate.

hm2FMActionParameter.name: hm2FMActionParameter
hm2FMActionParameter.description: This variable defines what acion to be done based on the value. By default it has value as none.

hm2FMActionSourceInterface.name: hm2FMActionSourceInterface
hm2FMActionSourceInterface.description: This variable defines the interface from which the source IP address will be taken for the file transfer session. The frames will not necessarily be sent on this interface, only the IP address of the interface will be used as source. By default it has value 0.

hm2FMProfileTable.name: hm2FMProfileTable
hm2FMProfileTable.description: A list of profiles stored in NV memory.

hm2FMProfileStorageType.name: hm2FMProfileStorageType
hm2FMProfileStorageType.description: Type of storage of the profile entry.

hm2FMProfileName.name: hm2FMProfileName
hm2FMProfileName.description: Name of the entry consisting of alphanumeric characters plus hyphen and underscore.

hm2FMProfileDateTime.name: hm2FMProfileDateTime
hm2FMProfileDateTime.description: Time and date of last write access using the content of the variable hm2SystemTime.

hm2FMProfileActive.name: hm2FMProfileActive
hm2FMProfileActive.description: Setting the variable to active(1) enables the profile so that it will be used the next time the configuration is reloaded. Setting the value to inactive(2) is not allowed since there must be always at least one profile with the state set to active(1).

hm2FMProfileAction.name: hm2FMProfileAction
hm2FMProfileAction.description: Action to be performed on the profile entry. Setting the value to delete(2) erases the profile. It is not possible to delete the currently active profile.

hm2FMProfileDeviceType.name: hm2FMProfileDeviceType
hm2FMProfileDeviceType.description: Manufacturer-defined product identifier (product family + product ID). Example: Object-ID 1.3.6.1.4.1.248.11.2.1.1 is the hm2ProductFamily EES and Object-ID 1.3.6.1.4.1.248.11.2.1.1.2 is the Product ID for ees25-0600

hm2FMProfileEncryptionActive.name: hm2FMProfileEncryptionActive
hm2FMProfileEncryptionActive.description: The profile is encrypted if this variable is set to active(true). It is not encrypted in case of inactive(false).

hm2FMProfileEncryptionVerified.name: hm2FMProfileEncryptionVerified
hm2FMProfileEncryptionVerified.description: This variable indicates true if an encrypted profile can be successfully decrypted by the device. In case of an encryption password mismatch, the verification fails the value is false. If the corresponding profile is not encrypted, this variable is set to true.

hm2FMProfileSwMajorRelNum.name: hm2FMProfileSwMajorRelNum
hm2FMProfileSwMajorRelNum.description: Shows the major release number of the firmware, the profile was created on.

hm2FMProfileSwMinorRelNum.name: hm2FMProfileSwMinorRelNum
hm2FMProfileSwMinorRelNum.description: Shows the minor release number of the firmware, the profile was created on.

hm2FMProfileSwBugfixRelNum.name: hm2FMProfileSwBugfixRelNum
hm2FMProfileSwBugfixRelNum.description: Shows the bugfix release number of the firmware, the profile was created on.

hm2FMProfileFingerprint.name: hm2FMProfileFingerprint
hm2FMProfileFingerprint.description: HEX String representation of profile content fingerprint. Consists of characters (0..9A..F) to represent a hexadecimal number. It will contain the string invalid, if the corresponding file does not contain a correct formatted SHA1 hash as fingerprint.

hm2FMProfileFingerprintVerified.name: hm2FMProfileFingerprintVerified
hm2FMProfileFingerprintVerified.description: This variable indicates true if the configuration profiles fingerprint matches the profile's configuration data. In case of a fingerprint, the variable is set to false.

hm2FMNvmState.name: hm2FMNvmState
hm2FMNvmState.description: This variable returns ok(1) if the contents of the currently used configuration is the same as that stored in NV memory or outOfsync(2) if there are any differences. The variable returns busy(3) if the process to determine a possible state change is currently running.

hm2FMEnvmState.name: hm2FMEnvmState
hm2FMEnvmState.description: This variable returns ok(1) if the contents of the currently used configuration on the active external non-volatile memory is the same than that stored in NV memory, outOfsync(2) if there are any differences. If the value is absent(3), then the external memory device is not connected.

hm2FMBootParamState.name: hm2FMBootParamState
hm2FMBootParamState.description: Returns outOfSync(2) if the boot parameters that were applied during startup are not in sync with the currently stored boot parameters, otherwise ok(1).

hm2ConfigWatchdogAdminStatus.name: hm2ConfigWatchdogAdminStatus
hm2ConfigWatchdogAdminStatus.description: Administrative status of the configuration watchdog. enable(1): start/trigger the watchdog timer disable(2): turn off the watchdog This feature provides recovery from situations where the device cannot be reached by the management station anymore. Whenever this variable is set to enable(1), the value of hm2ConfigWatchdogTimeInterval is loaded into the watchdog timer. This timer must be triggered before hm2ConfigWatchdogTimerValue reaches 0. If the watchdog timer expires, the last saved configuration of the device will be reapplied. The watchdog is triggered by MIB read and write accesses.

hm2ConfigWatchdogOperStatus.name: hm2ConfigWatchdogOperStatus
hm2ConfigWatchdogOperStatus.description: Operational status of the configuration watchdog. enable(1): watchdog up and running disable(2): watchdog inactive

hm2ConfigWatchdogTimeInterval.name: hm2ConfigWatchdogTimeInterval
hm2ConfigWatchdogTimeInterval.description: Period of the watchdog timer in seconds.

hm2ConfigWatchdogTimerValue.name: hm2ConfigWatchdogTimerValue
hm2ConfigWatchdogTimerValue.description: Current countdown value of the watchdog timer in seconds.

hm2ConfigWatchdogIPAddressType.name: hm2ConfigWatchdogIPAddressType
hm2ConfigWatchdogIPAddressType.description: IP address type of station that triggers the watchdog.

hm2ConfigWatchdogIPAddress.name: hm2ConfigWatchdogIPAddress
hm2ConfigWatchdogIPAddress.description: IP address of station that currently triggers the watchdog.

hm2FMServerUserName.name: hm2FMServerUserName
hm2FMServerUserName.description: Login name for the used file transport protocol.

hm2FMServerPassword.name: hm2FMServerPassword
hm2FMServerPassword.description: Password for the used file transport protocol.

hm2FileMgmtConfigPasswordStatus.name: hm2FileMgmtConfigPasswordStatus
hm2FileMgmtConfigPasswordStatus.description: Returns 'true' if a configuration password is set, otherwise 'false'.

hm2FileMgmtConfigPasswordChange.name: hm2FileMgmtConfigPasswordChange
hm2FileMgmtConfigPasswordChange.description: Password to encrypt confidential information in the configuration file. Format: '[old password]|[new password]' set password: '|[new password]' change password: '[old password]|[new password]' remove password: '[old password]|' Valid password characters are any DisplayString characters except '|'. When this object is read, the zero-length (empty) string is returned. Setting the zero-length string has no effect.

hm2FileMgmtGlobalSourceInterface.name: hm2FileMgmtGlobalSourceInterface
hm2FileMgmtGlobalSourceInterface.description: This variable defines the global source-interface used by file-transfers in case hm2FMActionSourceInterface is not configured by the user. The frames will not necessarily be sent on this interface, only the IP address of the interface will be used as source. By default it has value 0.

hm2FileMgmtConfigCompatibilityMode.name: hm2FileMgmtConfigCompatibilityMode
hm2FileMgmtConfigCompatibilityMode.description: Set 'hiosV1V2' only if a configuration file needs to be migrated to a device running HiOS 01.x.xx / 02.x.xx software. Otherwise for normal operation it is recommended to set the compatibility mode to the default 'disable'.

hm2FileMgmtSESCfgActivateSuccessSetFailu.name: hm2FileMgmtSESCfgActivateSuccessSetFailuresReturn
hm2FileMgmtSESCfgActivateSuccessSetFailu.description: Indicates a configuration profile was activated succesfully, but several config items failed to initialize.

hm2FileMgmtSESCfgActivateErrorReturn.name: hm2FileMgmtSESCfgActivateErrorReturn
hm2FileMgmtSESCfgActivateErrorReturn.description: Indicates a configuration profile could not be activated.

hm2FileMgmtSESCfgActivateIncomlpeteRetur.name: hm2FileMgmtSESCfgActivateIncomlpeteReturn
hm2FileMgmtSESCfgActivateIncomlpeteRetur.description: Indicates an incomlete activation of a configuration profile.

hm2FileMgmtSESCfgMgrCopyCommandErrorRetu.name: hm2FileMgmtSESCfgMgrCopyCommandErrorReturn
hm2FileMgmtSESCfgMgrCopyCommandErrorRetu.description: Indicates a failure of a COPY command given to the Config-Manager's command engine.

hm2FileMgmtSESCfgMgrClearCommandErrorRet.name: hm2FileMgmtSESCfgMgrClearCommandErrorReturn
hm2FileMgmtSESCfgMgrClearCommandErrorRet.description: Indicates a failure of a CLEAR command given to the Config-Manager's command engine.

hm2FileMgmtSESCfgMgrSwapCommandErrorRetu.name: hm2FileMgmtSESCfgMgrSwapCommandErrorReturn
hm2FileMgmtSESCfgMgrSwapCommandErrorRetu.description: Indicates a failure of a SWAP command given to the Config-Manager's command engine.

hm2FileMgmtSESCfgMgrCommandActivateError.name: hm2FileMgmtSESCfgMgrCommandActivateErrorReturn
hm2FileMgmtSESCfgMgrCommandActivateError.description: Indicates a failure because other Config-Manager command is running.

hm2ConfigurationSavedTrap.name: hm2ConfigurationSavedTrap
hm2ConfigurationSavedTrap.description: This trap is sent after the configuration of the agent was successfully saved.

hm2ConfigurationChangedTrap.name: hm2ConfigurationChangedTrap
hm2ConfigurationChangedTrap.description: This trap is sent if there is a change in the synchronization status between currently running and the saved configuration so that the value of hm2FMNvmState changes.
